President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key posts at the Treasury Department: David S. Cohen as Assistant Secretary of Treasury for Terrorist Financing, Alan B. Krueger as Assistant Secretary of Treasury for Economic Policy, and Kim N. Wallace as Assistant Secretary of Treasury for Legislative Affairs. Each of the nominees is currently serving as a Counselor to the Secretary of Treasury. David Cohen is a former partner at law firm WilmerHale, with experience in civil litigation, criminal defense, and anti-money laundering counseling. Alan Krueger is a professor of economics and public affairs at Princeton University, with expertise in education, unemployment, income distribution, and terrorism. Kim Wallace has worked in the Washington Research Group at Barclays Capital and Lehman Brothers, and has legislative experience specializing in fiscal policy.